Turkish Equity Movers: Ford Otosan, Isbank, Goodyear, Ulker Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-02-15T15:10:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/turkish-equity-movers-ford-otosan-isbank-goodyear-ulker-move.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index  gained 466.28, or 0.7 percent, to 65,035.14 at 4:30 p.m.
in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS (FROTO TI), Ford Motor Co.’s
Turkish unit, rose 20 kurus, or 1.5 percent, to 13.80 liras. The
company reported 2010 profit of 571 million liras ($359 million)
in 2010, up 51 percent, in a filing to the exchange for tax
purposes.    Turkiye Is Bankasi  AS (ISCTR TI), Turkey’s largest listed
bank by assets, rose 6 kurus, or 1.2 percent, to 5.26 liras. The
bank reported 2010 profit of 2.98 billion liras, up 26 percent
over 2009, in a filing for tax purposes after the market closed
yesterday.    Goodyear Lastikleri Turk AS  (GOODY TI), a tiremaker, rose
to a record high, surging 2.7 liras, or 9.2 percent, to 32.10
liras. The company reported 2010 profit of 38.2 million liras in
a tax filing today.    Ulker Biskuvi Sanayi AS  (ULKER TI), a Turkish producer of
biscuits and chocolate bars, rose 30 kurus, or 5.7 percent, to
5.70 liras. The company’s tax financials showed a profit of
208.4 million liras in 2010, up 52 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  